50|$|Academic {{work since}} 2012 {{demonstrated}} {{the feasibility of}} <b>steganography</b> for Cyber-physical systems (CPS)/the Internet of Things (IoT). Some techniques of CPS/IoT <b>steganography</b> overlap with network <b>steganography,</b> i.e. hiding data in communication protocols used in CPS/the IoT. However, specific techniques hide data in CPS components. For instance, data {{can be stored in}} unsued registers of IoT/CPS components and in the states of IoT/CPS actuators.|$|E
