5000|$|<b>Steganography</b> is a {{technique}} where information or files are hidden within another file {{in an attempt to}} hide data by leaving it in plain sight. [...] "Steganography produces dark data that is typically buried within light data (e.g., a non-perceptible digital watermark buried within a digital photograph)." [...] Some experts have argued that the use of <b>steganography</b> techniques are not very widespread and therefore shouldn't be given a lot of thought. Most experts will agree that <b>steganography</b> has the capability of disrupting the forensic process when used correctly.|$|E
